        "id": 267460,
        "name": "",
        "username": "Matt069",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/d2c977/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-05-04T12:34:55.037Z",
        "cooked": "<p>That to follow, why not skip server all along and go into direct call over internet ? We do not need server in place if peer-to-peer communication occurs. Server could be there as backup when P2P is not possible or limited.</p>\n<p>I often call my family members in another county, we both use Fibre internet with WiFi. I see that video call is much degraded in comparison to FaceTime, WhatsApp and Teams.</p>\n<p>It would be great to be able to choose what is your priority (detail, speed or bandwidth). There are several ways to reduce size : lower resolution, lower fps, different compression, fewer key frames) I would be happy with 20-30 fps and a little higher resolution as in HD (often it looks like 340p at 60 fps). I do not need 4k at 60 fps video call <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
